# Third-party raw corpora — NEVER commit these.
# DATA_PROVENANCE.md policy: "ship loader code + DOIs, not re-hosted corpora".
# src/dataset_v2.py reconstructs every one of these from its original source, so
# committing them re-hosts data we do not have redistribution rights to AND adds
# ~432MB to the repo. Self-generated data under data/raw/ (our own synthetic
# phishing) IS tracked — that is our own work.
data/raw/spamassassin/
data/raw/enron/
data/raw/spamassassin_full/
data/raw/trec07/
data/raw/multi_llm/
data/raw/phishing_email_dataset/

# Regenerated by notebook 06 §15 on every run; no need to version it.
data/processed/_robustness_subsample.csv
# 493MB of parquet, byte-identical to what load_enron_clean() fetches from HuggingFace
# and caches. Re-hosting it would also break the "ship loaders + DOIs, not corpora"
# policy in DATA_PROVENANCE.md.
data/corbt-enron-emails/

